participating-org.narrative:
AJOAGO was founded in January 2001 in Govuro District, Inhambane Province.

AJOAGO is a legal person of private law, without profit, fostering socio-economic and community development vulnerable rural, with legal personality and administrative autonomy,
financialand asset.

AJOAGO not pursue ends that have any identification political - party, ethnic, tribal, regional or social exclusion by their various forms
The AJOAGO aims to contribute to the eradication of absolute poverty and the factors inherent.

AJOAGO aims:
Contribute to reducing disaster risk strengthening the processes of prevention, response and mitigation of vulnerable communities;
Contribute to improving the livelihoods of poor people;
Fostering capacity of the institutions andfor local adaptation and mitigate the climatic diversity.
Promote gender equity, right to life and dignity on HIV - AIDS.
Advocate the government to make decisions that lead to change and / or improvement governance, at all levels, so to benefit citizens;
Develop individual skills and institutional toanswer organizational growthneeds.

Main interventions areas:
Sustainable Livelihoods;
Disaster Risk Reduction;
Adaptation and Mitigation climate change;
Children and Youth.
Gender and HIV - AIDS and;
Advocacy and Governance.
